source.name: Survey of Groundfish  Ages in Alaska, 1980-2011
source.description: This collection is from the RACE survey dataset where specimens were collected during groundfish trawl and acoustic surveys.  The Age and Growth Program is a service organization that provides age data that contributes to our basic understanding of a species whether it is in the context of sustainable fisheries, species conservation, or species ecology. The program is primarily focused on age data for age structured modeling of exploited fish populations.
